The paper deals with the task of generating a well-structured overview report (ORPT) over thousands of related documents, which involves techniques such as text filtering, keyword scoring, single-document summarization (SDS), topic modeling, multi-document summarization (MDS), and title generation. These techniques are commonly used in the fields of information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
